      { heading: "Where MerrySails is not the right answer", content: "An honest comparison includes the cases where MerrySails is not the best fit. The shared cruises do not work for guests who want a 6-person private boat with their own guide — for that, a smaller local operator with a single-vessel licence is usually a better match. The yacht charter range tops out at the 40-guest group yacht, which is excellent for proposals, family cruising, and mid-size corporate events but not the right fit for 100+ guest gala bookings or ultra-luxury €2,000+ charters with full event production — those briefs belong to dedicated event-vessel charter brokers.\n\nThe public Şehir Hatları ferry is also a real option that this guide will not pretend doesn't exist. For €1.20 you can cross the Bosphorus on a public ferry; you will not get a guide, snacks, sunset timing, or a covered upper deck, but you will be on the water. If the trip is about transit and not about the cruise experience, that is the right pick.\n\nFinally, MerrySails publishes prices in EUR. If a guest is locked into a strict TRY-only budget or wants to book through a Turkish concierge desk specifically, the concierge layer adds a 30–50% markup; in that case the OTA argument flips — the concierge markup is much higher than the OTA markup, and direct booking saves more, not less." }
